# ── LLM brain ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The app degrades gracefully: with NO keys it runs a deterministic MOCK model
# (great for offline dev + the /demo fixtures). Pick ONE live path for real runs:
#
# (a) Vercel AI Gateway  — recommended. In production on Vercel, nothing is
#     needed (VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN is injected automatically; bare "anthropic/..."
#     model ids route through the gateway on Vercel credits). For LOCAL live runs:
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=
#
# (b) Direct Anthropic key (overrides the gateway path when set):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#
# MODEL_MODE=auto            # auto | live | mock   (auto = live if any key/OIDC)

# ── Live web provider ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Primary = Nimble (sponsor). Get a key (5,000 free credits) at
# https://online.nimbleway.com/signup → dashboard → API Keys.
# NIMBLE_API_KEY=
# JINA_API_KEY=             # optional: enables s.jina.ai search in the fallback
# WEB_PROVIDER=auto         # auto | nimble | jina | mock
#   auto = Nimble (if NIMBLE_API_KEY) with keyless Jina/DuckDuckGo fallback.

# ── Receipt signing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. If unset, an ephemeral ECDSA P-256 key is generated per process
# (fine for a single instance). For stable cross-instance verification, set:
# RECEIPT_SIGNING_JWK={"kty":"EC","crv":"P-256",...}
#   Generate one with:  node scripts/gen-key.mjs
